---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import PageHero from "../components/PageHero.astro";

// Terms of Service. [BRACKETED] items need the registered company details.
// Not legal advice — have a qualified lawyer review before relying on it.
const updated = "21 July 2026";
---

<BaseLayout
  current="home"
  title="Terms of Service — Coworking Prilep"
  description="The terms that govern membership, bookings, payments, and use of the Coworking Prilep space and website."
>
  <PageHero
    eyebrow="Legal"
    title="Terms of Service"
    subtitle="The terms that govern your membership, bookings, payments, and use of our space and website."
  />

  <article class="px-6 pb-24 md:px-12 md:pb-32">
    <div class="prose-cws mx-auto max-w-3xl">
      <p class="font-mono text-[11px] tracking-[0.25em] text-bone/40 uppercase">
        Last updated: {updated}
      </p>

      <h2>1. Who we are</h2>
      <p>
        Coworking Prilep is operated by <strong>Dastian DOO Prilep</strong>
        (registered seat: Kej 1-vi Maj no. 9, Prilep; ЕДБ 4021025551046, ЕМБС 7821808),
        through its branch <strong>BLOK 02</strong> at Jane Sandanski no. 33, Prilep,
        North Macedonia ("we", "us"). These Terms of Service ("Terms") govern your use
        of our coworking space, our services, and this website (coworkingprilep.mk).
      </p>

      <h2>2. Acceptance</h2>
      <p>
        By buying a membership, pass, or booking, or by using the space or the
        website, you agree to these Terms, our <a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a>,
        <a href="/refunds">Refund Policy</a>, and <a href="/delivery">Delivery
        Policy</a>. If you don't agree, please don't use the service.
      </p>

      <h2>3. Our services</h2>
      <p>
        We provide access to a shared workspace and its facilities — dedicated
        desks, hot desks, a meeting room, a classroom, internet access, and related
        amenities — subject to availability and the plan you choose. Opening hours,
        facilities, and access rules are as published at the space and on the
        website and may change.
      </p>

      <h2>4. Membership &amp; access</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Memberships and passes are <strong>personal and non-transferable</strong>. Do not share your access credentials, keycard, or code.</li>
        <li>You are responsible for all activity under your account and access.</li>
        <li>Where 24/7 or keycard access is offered, you must follow the access and security rules and not let unauthorised people in ("tailgating").</li>
        <li>You must be at least 18 years old to hold a membership.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>5. Bookings</h2>
      <p>
        Meeting room and classroom bookings are for the date, time, and capacity you
        reserve. Cancellation and refund terms for bookings are set out in our
        <a href="/refunds">Refund Policy</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>6. Payments &amp; fees</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Memberships and passes are paid <strong>in advance</strong>. Card payments are processed securely through ProCredit Bank's Virtual POS; we do not store your card details.</li>
        <li>Prices are shown at checkout. We may change prices with reasonable notice; changes do not affect a period you have already paid for.</li>
        <li>Unpaid or failed renewals may lead to suspension of access until payment is resolved.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>7. Refunds</h2>
      <p>
        Refunds and cancellations are governed by our
        <a href="/refunds">Refund Policy</a>, which reflects your rights under the
        Law on Consumer Protection of North Macedonia.
      </p>

      <h2>8. Acceptable use &amp; house rules</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Use the space lawfully and with respect for other members and staff.</li>
        <li>No harassment, threatening behaviour, excessive noise, or activity that disturbs others.</li>
        <li>No illegal activity, and no using the space or internet for unlawful purposes.</li>
        <li>Keep shared areas clean and treat the furniture, equipment, and premises with care.</li>
        <li>Guests are your responsibility and must follow these Terms.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>9. Your belongings</h2>
      <p>
        You are responsible for your personal belongings. To the extent permitted by
        law, we are not liable for loss of, or damage to, items you bring to the
        space. You are responsible for any damage you (or your guests) cause to the
        premises or equipment.
      </p>

      <h2>10. Internet</h2>
      <p>
        Internet access is provided on a best-effort, "as-is" basis. We do not
        guarantee uptime, speed, or security, and you must not use the network for
        illegal downloading, unauthorised access, or any activity that harms the
        network or other users.
      </p>

      <h2>11. Health &amp; safety</h2>
      <p>
        Follow all posted safety instructions and the reasonable directions of our
        staff. We may deny or withdraw access where health, safety, or security
        require it.
      </p>

      <h2>12. Intellectual property</h2>
      <p>
        The Coworking Prilep name, brand, website, and content are owned by us or our
        licensors and may not be copied or used without permission. You keep
        ownership of your own work and materials.
      </p>

      <h2>13. Limitation of liability</h2>
      <p>
        To the maximum extent permitted by law, we are not liable for indirect or
        consequential loss, loss of business, data, or profit arising from your use
        of the space, services, or website. Nothing in these Terms limits liability
        that cannot be limited by law, including your statutory consumer rights.
      </p>

      <h2>14. Suspension &amp; termination</h2>
      <p>
        We may suspend or end your access for breach of these Terms, unpaid fees, or
        behaviour that endangers or seriously disturbs others. Where we end your
        membership without cause, any refund is handled under our
        <a href="/refunds">Refund Policy</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>15. Changes</h2>
      <p>
        We may update our services and these Terms from time to time. The current
        version is always published here with its "last updated" date; continued use
        after a change means you accept the updated Terms.
      </p>

      <h2>16. Governing law &amp; disputes</h2>
      <p>
        These Terms are governed by the laws of the <strong>Republic of North
        Macedonia</strong>. We'll always try to resolve any issue with you directly
        first. Any dispute that cannot be resolved is subject to the jurisdiction of
        the competent court in North Macedonia, without affecting the mandatory
        consumer-protection rights available to you.
      </p>

      <h2>17. Contact</h2>
      <p>
        Dastian DOO Prilep, Kej 1-vi Maj no. 9, Prilep, North Macedonia ·
        <a href="mailto:coworkingprilep@outlook.com">coworkingprilep@outlook.com</a>
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
